<h5>Do not Assume that all Druids Want CH and ManaBurn!<br>
<br>
A Summary of the Thread is located here: <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showMessage?topicID=15.topic" target="_blank">Summary of the Cleric/Druid Brainstorming</a></h5><br>
**I am sorry I had to Edit this post but after reading post from this community and other communities, people feel that they can comment on the entire thread without reading it and "assume" way to much** - Sobe</b><br>
<br>
<hr><b>Continue on with this Unknown Druids Post...</b><br>
<br>
<u>I've concluded</u> druids need Complete Heal and Manaburn.  Uber guilds dont' want us, raids don't need us, and while we have great fun soloing we don't do a whole heck of a lot for anybody else.  CH is broken but unless the game is fixed to not revolve around this spell it's either join in or get out.  Manaburn has it's nice points but mostly this is a "my dic... er nuke is bigger than yours" spell, and is more flash than bang but oh what a pretty flash.<br>
 <br>
  There is a reason uber guilds recruit as many clerics and as many wizards as they can get their hands on and start to turn up their nose or refuse more than 2 druids.  Take a look at any of the top guild rosters and you'll see endless ranks of clerics and growing ranks of wizards and while the shaman / magician / enchanter ranks aren't overwhelming no one questions that they are there and necessary.  Druids however are bench space that everyone else wishes was a cleric or wizard instead.<br>
 <br>
  Druids usually fill the role of healer.  Amazingly with 6 or 8 clerics on a raid (and them chewing rods like mad from the shaman/magician factory) there is still need for druids to heal, even though our 60 heal is less efficient than a level 34 cleric's and by the time a cleric hits 39 they're easily far and away outhealing the 60 druid on the raid.  So obviously there is something wrong here.  Despite the overabundance of clerics, healing is STILL required, so either clerics can't heal well enough so druids have to fill in with their insignificant heals, or druids (and others) don't heal well enough that there must be so many clerics around.  I've stated druids should get CH so you know which one I think it is.  When the very first question when a target is reported up is "how many clerics do we have" and then "how many clerics can people 2box/ditch their primary character and play a cleric instead" and this determining whether or not we get the mob I think it pretty clear that the broken CH and the game's reliance on it is causing problems.  I don't see VI fixing this and as much as I'd prefer a different solution I see druids getting CH as the best thing for the class and the game.<br>
 <br>
  Giving druids CH also kills a 2nd bird with the same stone.  Mid 50's druids are in a very bad situation for healing.  Without a slower in the group they simply cannot keep up healing a group that is getting a decent xp rate without seriously twinked tanks.  Although not a great in-combat heal for druids since we lack low agro pulse heals and divine aura/barriar and plate armor and the extra HPs afforded by armor and symbol so we won't live through casting this often, it would make an excellent downtime heal that would keep the party going instead of staring at the druid waiting for her mana to regen and wondering how soon they can kick her out for that cleric or shaman shouting LFG at the zoneline.<br>
 <br>
  What is manaburn?  Manaburn is a 6 second cast 144 minute refresh class AA that empties the wizard's manapool and converts it into a nuke doing approximatly 2 damage per mana (I believe it's randomly 1.6 to 2.2) that can be critted and works with focus items giving a 7k nuke to your typical wizard and potentially over 24k nuke to an "uber" equipped wizard that gets very lucky.  It is unresistable and has the same agro as dealing a single point of damage (basically no agro.)  It also works in PvP for full or near enough damage that even buffed tanks usually die to it and non warriors have no chance.  Necromancers have a somewhat similar AA called Lifeburn.<br>
 <br>
  Manaburn is... overrated, but despite this is so sought after and drooled over it puts wizards into a heavily desired position.  While great for KSing Ragefire and other "old" mobs (so is Atone and memblur) and good for those very high resist mobs that you can't land anything on otherwise or don't want to be anywhere near their AE (Tunare etc.) it is mostly good for stopping a mob from gating or cutting through enrage.  On mobs with seemingly 500k or more HPs where it takes 10 to 20 minutes of beating on the mob tossing your mana away in a 2.6 damage/mana nuke is pretty dumb when you can use moonfire, wildfire etc. and be doing about 6 damage/mana (more if you're a wizard!)  So while it's not going to infringe on wizards with their bigger manapools, higher manaregen, much higher DPS, more efficient and varied nukes, it will make druids more desired and give us an excuse as to why we can't be in the CH chain...  =)<br>
 <br>
  So as it stands a raid is better off for the most part by adding a 39 cleric than a 60 druid and while druids aren't nearly as far off wizards for effectiveness as we are clerics, we are nowhere close to being as desired as them and lacking unresistable damage still face the occasional raid/fight we can contribute nothing at. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usobesilvertree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sobe Silvertree</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/16/02 5:29:04 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uellzii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellzii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333399>(7/9/02 7:57:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> There is not enough for a druid to do</span><hr size=1> Top Tier guild reopened recruiting yesterday on my server. Looking for ENC MAG ROG RAN CLR BRD<br>
