<br>
In these "well balanced" levels, druids maintain a certain percentage of the power possessed by the classes at the top of the charts in certain areas.  In our strong areas, this percentage is in the 65% to 85% range.  This includes DDs, DoTs, and Healing.   We have skills in other areas, of course, like charming, but our relative power is below 50% in most cases.<br>
<br>
The "Druid Problem" is that our relative power in our strong areas has dropped dramatically by the time we reach 60.  This is especially evident in high level raids.  Healing is, perhaps, the most egregious example, but is not the only one.  Moreover, our relative power in our other areas has generally dropped as well (e.g., we were pretty even with wizards with regard to gating/porting, but we now have dropped to 60% or so, in my opinion).<br>
<br>
My logic is this: since we were balanced before at our old power percentages, we will maintain that balance if we maintain those same relative power percentages.<br>
<br>
And that's all I think most druids want.  To maintain their same relative position vis a vis other classes.<br>
<br>
With that in mind, druids cannot get CH and Manaburn as they currently are implemented.  They really establish the 100% power ranking for Clerics and Wizards.  Druids need improvements in both healing and DDs, but only to the point of restoring the class to its proper relative power in these areas.<br>
