I have yet to see a single GOOD reason why Druids should get Complete Heal.  Am I defensive over this spell?  You better believe that I am.  It's been done MANY times before but I'm going to do it again.<br>
<br>
Why would ANYONE play a Cleric if they could play a Druid with Complete Heal?  It is, quite literally, the ONLY thing we get.  Buffs?  Other classes can buff quite easily and effectively in non-raid situations.  For a Raid situation, bring out a single Cleric who has been PLd to 60 and MGB the entire Raid with Aego and then camp him.  Resses?  Paladins and Necros can Rez as well so this isn't the sole territory of Clerics anymore.  Once again, if the Raid wipes just log on your two PLd Clerics with Epics and res the Raid back in.  The ONLY thing that a Cleric has going for him/her is Complete Heal.<br>
<br>
